               <p>JAMES HENRY EAST. This is my glass - the prisoner was the last person I should have suspected of robbing me; I gave him leave to lodge on my premises till he could get a place.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had no intention of robbing him - I had done business with him, and for him, for ten years.</p>
